'''Ida Bagus Oka''' (16 April 1936 &ndash; March 7, 2010 <ref>http://www.balidiscovery.com/messages/message.asp?Id=5869</ref>) was the Governor of [[Bali]], Indonesia from 1988 to 1993. He was also a [[Development Reform Cabinet#State Ministers|State Minister of Population/Chairman of Planned Families National Coordinating Body]] in the [[Development Reform Cabinet]] under [[Jusuf Habibie]].  During the [[Indonesian killings of 1965–1966]], Ida Bagus Oka instigated the Balinese [[Hinduism|Hindus]]  to hunt down PKI supporters.  He told Hindus: "There can be no doubt [that] the enemies of our revolution are also the cruelest enemies of religion, and must be eliminated and destroyed down to the roots".[https://books.google.com/books?id=lSU3mFK1gMUC&printsec=frontcover&dq=Making+Indonesia+By+George+McTurnan+Kahin,+Daniel+S.+Lev&ei=tNmyS-y-AYKOkATSjMibDQ&cd=1#v=onepage&q=Ida%20Bagus%20Oka&f=false]  During this period, an estimated 80,000 Balinese were killed, roughly 5 percent of the island's population at the time.[https://books.google.com/books?id=_w6Mn4xRLt8C&pg=PA92&dq=Friend,+T.+(2003).+Indonesian+Destinies.&ei=YtqyS_7cJ4bqlQSNqozNBw&cd=1#v=onepage&q=Bali&f=false].  In 2001, Oka was convicted in a corruption case involving  Rp. 2.3 billion and was sentenced for one year.

