'''Thristan Mendoza''' (born 1989) is a [[Philippines|Filipino]] [[autistic savant]] and [[marimba]] prodigy.
Thristan "Tum-Tum" Mendoza was born 1989 in [[Quezon City]], [[Philippines]]. He was enrolled at the Philippine Montessori Center and was diagnosed as [[autism|autistic]] at the age of two and a half. During the same year he began to play.
In 1997 the University of the Philippines presented him as a gifted child prodigy.
He is now a college student majoring in percussion.
He has three siblings (Rainier, Victoria Angela, Victorina Francesca)
