{{Infobox MLA |name = Vasanbhai Ahir |office = Member of [[Gujarat Legislative Assembly]] |term_start1 = 2007 |term_end1 = 2012 |constituency1 = [[Bhuj (Vidhan Sabha constituency)|Bhuj]] |term_start2 = 2012 and 2017 |term_end2 = Incumbent |constituency2 = [[Ratna (Vidhan Sabha constituency)|Anjar]] | nationality = Indian | party = [[Bhartiya Janata Party]] |religion = [[Hindu]] }} '''Vasanbhai Ahir''' is a [[Member of Legislative assembly|member]] of [[Gujarat Legislative Assembly]] from [[Anjar (Vidhan Sabha constituency)|Anjar]] constituency for 13th assembly since December 2012 and 2017. He formerly represented [[Bhuj (Vidhan Sabha constituency)|Bhuj]] constituency in 12th assembly from 2007 to 2012.<ref>{{cite web|title=TWELFTH GUJARAT LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY|url=http://www.gujaratassembly.gov.in/emembers12.htm|publisher=Gujarat assembly|accessdate=19 May 2012}}</ref>
He started his political career right from the grass root level of Indian democracy that is [[Gram Panchayat]]. He was elected as Sarpanch of [[Ratnal]] (a village between [[Anjar, India|Anjar]] and [[Bhuj]] in [[Kutch district]]).
