{{Portal|Book of Mormon}}
According to the [[Book of Mormon]], '''Zeram''' ({{IPAc-en|ˈ|z|iː|r|ə|m}}),<ref>[http://www.lds.org/scriptures/bofm/pronunciation?lang=eng LDS.org: "Book of Mormon Pronunciation Guide"] (retrieved 2012-02-25), [[Wikipedia:IPA for English|IPA]]-ified from «zē´rum»</ref> '''Amnor''' ({{IPAc-en|ˈ|æ|m|n|ɔr}}),<ref>[http://www.lds.org/scriptures/bofm/pronunciation?lang=eng LDS.org: "Book of Mormon Pronunciation Guide"] (retrieved 2012-02-25), [[Wikipedia:IPA for English|IPA]]-ified from «ăm´nōr»</ref> '''Manti''' ({{IPAc-en|ˈ|m|æ|n|t|aɪ}}),<ref>[http://www.lds.org/scriptures/bofm/pronunciation?lang=eng LDS.org: "Book of Mormon Pronunciation Guide"] (retrieved 2012-02-25), [[Wikipedia:IPA for English|IPA]]-ified from «măn´tī»</ref> and '''Limher''' ({{IPAc-en|ˈ|l|ɪ|m|h|ər}})<ref>[http://www.lds.org/scriptures/bofm/pronunciation?lang=eng LDS.org: "Book of Mormon Pronunciation Guide"] (retrieved 2012-02-25), [[Wikipedia:IPA for English|IPA]]-ified from «lĭm´her»</ref> were [[Nephite]] spies who lived in the 1st century BC{{citation needed|date=October 2012}}, and, under the direction of [[Alma the Younger|Alma]], were sent to spy on the camp of the [[Amlicites]] during the war between the Nephites and that people.<ref>[http://scriptures.lds.org/en/alma/2/22#22 Alma 2:22]</ref> These four spies witnessed the joining of the Amlicites with the [[Lamanite]]s, and reported to the event to Alma, after which the Nephite army hastened back to [[Zarahemla]] in retreat.

